{"parse":{"title":"R. S. Sugirtharajah","pageid":55599278,"revid":814232823,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Rasiah S. Sugirtharajah</b>, known as <b>R. S. Sugirtharajah</b>, is a <a href=\"/wiki/Biblical_hermeneutics\" title=\"Biblical hermeneutics\">biblical hermeneuticist</a> and an emeritus professor at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Birmingham\" title=\"University of Birmingham\">University of Birmingham</a>. He is known for his work in developing the field of <a href=\"/wiki/Postcolonial_theology#Biblical_criticism\" title=\"Postcolonial theology\">postcolonial biblical criticism</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Biography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Biography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Works</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=R._S._Sugirtharajah&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Born in <a href=\"/wiki/Sri_Lanka\" title=\"Sri Lanka\">Sri Lanka</a>, Sugirtharajah pursued his <a href=\"/wiki/Bachelor_of_Divinity\" title=\"Bachelor of Divinity\">Bachelor of Divinity</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Hiwale_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hiwale-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_Theology\" title=\"Master of Theology\">Master of Theology</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Hiwale_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hiwale-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> degrees at <a href=\"/wiki/United_Theological_College,_Bangalore\" title=\"United Theological College, Bangalore\">United Theological College, Bangalore</a> {affiliated to the <a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Senate of Serampore College (University)</a>} in <a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">India</a> before completing his <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Doctor of Philosophy\">Doctor of Philosophy</a> degree at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Birmingham\" title=\"University of Birmingham\">University of Birmingham</a> in England.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He is best known for his work in introducing postcolonial criticism to the study of the Bible, in works such as <i>Asian Biblical Hermeneutics and Postcolonialism</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Sugirtharajah1998_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sugirtharajah1998-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and <i>Postcolonial Critism and Biblical Interpretation</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sugirtharajah2002_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sugirtharajah2002-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He is also known for bringing to the foreground marginalized voices which are rarely heard in mainstream studies of Christianity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2009, a volume was published in Sugirtharajah's honour entitled <i>Postcolonial Interventions</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Liew2009_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Liew2009-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=R._S._Sugirtharajah&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Sugirtharajah, R. S. (1991). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=zLPYAAAAMAAJ\"><i>Voices from the Margin: Interpreting the Bible in the Third World</i></a>. London: SPCK. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-281-04506-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-281-04506-8\">978-0-281-04506-8</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Voices+from+the+Margin%3A+Interpreting+the+Bible+in+the+Third+World&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=SPCK&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-281-04506-8&amp;rft.aulast=Sugirtharajah&amp;rft.aufirst=R.+S.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DzLPYAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AR.+S.+Sugirtharajah\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Sugirtharajah, R. S. (1998). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=pc0-Ezlp2iAC\"><i>Asian Biblical Hermeneutics and Postcolonialism: Contesting the Interpretations</i></a>. Maryknoll, New York: Orbis Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-85075-973-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-85075-973-7\">978-1-85075-973-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abo